Introduction My memory goes back ~ years /maɪ ˈmɛməri goʊz bæk ~ jɪərz/: This phrase is used to express that one can remember something from a certain number of years ago.
&ldquo;My memory goes back 20 years, to the first charity event I ever organized.&rdquo;
My memory goes back to my childhood /maɪ ˈmɛməri goʊz bæk tuː maɪ ˈʧaɪldhʊd/: This phrase is used when one is recalling events from their childhood.
